7. Now we can argue what "doing good" really is. That's fair. But we can't say we are doing right when we do wrong.
6. The "good guys" are good to the extent they do good. Not because they wear white hats (or put an R or D after their names).
5. My hate is ok because it trumps their hate. My lies are okay because they trump their lies. Thus we become haters and liars.

3. To reject arrogance is to say "There is no inherent line between 'good' and 'bad' people. Everyone has the capacity to do evil."
